      "content": "The argument for minimum wage increases is fundamentally about supporting the working class and injecting necessary spending power into local economies. When low-wage workers earn more, they spend that extra money locally on goods and services, which directly benefits small businesses. While large chains have more capital to absorb costs, the increased demand from higher-earning local employees provides a genuine economic boost that benefits the entire community.",
