      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The concern that higher wages lead to higher prices is a predictable, short-term reaction, but it doesn't negate the long-term economic benefits of a healthier workforce. Small businesses that adapt by improving efficiency and service quality can thrive, while those that fail are simply not sustainable in a modern economy. The theory is sound because a more equitable wage floor creates a more robust and stable consumer base for everyone in town.",
      "source": "target",
